    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-01-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="114"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d114">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_FEAC1"
                    >FEAC</gloss>/1–746: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Certain
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives Abroad</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="23" xml:id="d114fn1">At Canberra, Chungking, London, Moscow, New Delhi,
                        Ottawa, Paris, The Hague, and Wellington.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-01-07">January 7,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>View this Govt that Far Eastern Commission succeeded Far Eastern Advisory
                    Commission Dec 27, date Moscow communiqué,<note n="24" xml:id="d114fn2">For text
                        of communiqué issued by the Foreign Ministers on December 27, 1945, see <ref
                            target="frus1945v02#pg_815">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1945, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 815</ref>, or Department of State <hi
                            rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, December 30, 1945, p. 1027.</note> and
                    therefore no need to implement succession by formal dissolution, inauguration or
                    other formalities.</p>
                <p>Convey above informally <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>, explaining
                    this Govt’s position based solely on desire to free Commission from confusing
                    and burdensome procedural detail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
